1. Convert the image preferred for logo to ppm format using any image converter

2. Install Netpbm package using the following command, if it is not installed
        sudo apt-get install netpbm

3. Reduce the number of colors in the image to 224 
	ppmquant 224 boot_logo_a.ppm > boot_logo_224.ppm

4. Convert it to PPMASCII format
	pnmnoraw boot_logo_224.ppm > boot_logo_ascii_224.ppm

5. Use boot_logo_ascii_224.ppm as logo image
